Create tables:

CREATE TABLE aluno (
	id SERIAL primary key,
	name varchar(80)
);

CREATE TABLE notas (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    idaluno integer references aluno (id),
    n1 real,
    n2 real,
    n3 real,
    n4 real,
    media real
);

create a .env file in each folder with the database configuration.
Exemple:
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=(...)
DB_NAME=(...)
DB_PASSWORD=(...)
DB_PORT=(...)
PORT=(3000 teacher side - 8080 student side)

#API Documentation:

When starting the "teacher" and "student" application, access "http://localhost:3000/api-doc/" 
to read the documentation and use the project.